Younis Mohammed Ibrahim al-Hayari

Younis Mohammed Ibrahim al-Hayari is a citizen of Morocco who was reported killed in a shootout with Saudi Arabian security officials on July 3, 2005.
The gunfight took place in Rawda.
At the time of his reported death Younis was at the top of Saudi Arabia's most wanted list.
At the time of his death he was described as the head of Al Qaeda in Saudi Arabia.

