<doc id="21378552" url="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=21378552" title="Mina ngo hlala nginje">
Mina ngo hlala nginje

"Mina ngo hlala nginje" is the 2009 election song of South Africa's African National Congress (ANC). Composed, produced and arranged by Chicco Twala, and performed by Winnie Khumalo, its title is translated into English as "I will remain an ANC for life".
The ANC advertised the song via its official "Facebook" page on 27 January 2009, through a message sent out to group members by Senzi Ngubane.

