<doc id="21379704" url="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=21379704" title="Passion (2005 film)">
Passion (2005 film)

Passion or Bab al-Makam () (International title: "Passion") is a Syrian feature drama film by director Mohamed Malas.
The film presents a highly critical view of a rabidly patriarchal society. In the film, Amine (Salwa Jamil) is a Syrian woman whose passion for music becomes her fall. In traditional Islamic society, a respectable woman equals a silent woman - but Amine refuses to abide by such rules. Rather than live in dishonor, her own family decides to do away with her.

