The title refers to the .
"Karasu: 13 Japanese Birds Pt. 4".
The title refers to the .
"Uzura: 13 Japanese Birds Pt. 5".
The title refers to the . The song titles refer to a March 2009 cull after the bird flu virus was found.
"Kamo: 13 Japanese Birds Pt. 6".
The title refers to the . The cover depicts the Tufted Duck. The first track is a protest against the wild-bird cull instituted by Tokyo Governor Shintarō Ishihara. Akasaka is a district in Minato, Tokyo.
"Kujakubato: 13 Japanese Birds Pt. 7".
The title refers to the . The bird design on the cover was previously used on "Fantail". The album was delayed until the first week of August.
"Kokuchou: 13 Japanese Birds Pt. 8".
The title refers to the . "Ushiwaka 2" is a reworking of a track from "Yoshinotsune".
